text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
and so it begins. 
i used to love going to walks on my own. to clear my head and get ideas. 
but now i am too afraid. to many times have groups of grown men in cars trailed me and tried to pull me in.

and that is not ok. this is not ok. we can't live in fear forever.
especially knowing that the justice system is also slow and the conviction rate so low.

the amount of times i could have reported someone for sexual assault or rape is just beyond a joke. 
and yet i was always scared of what they would do to me, if the justice system failed 'because they have dependants, because they have a career.' i was scared i would end up dead.

not going out running alone does not solve sexual assault and rape. it's everywhere. 
it's even in your home at the hands of your partner.

telling women to not be free is not the answer. there being a serious and absolute penalty for this kind of behaviour is.

name: Steph
tweet_full:
and so it begins. 
i used to love going to walks on my own. to clear my head and get ideas. 
but now i am too afraid. to many times have groups of grown men in cars trailed me and tried to pull me in.

and that is not ok. this is not ok. we can not live in fear forever.
especially knowing that the justice system is also slow and the conviction rate so low.

the amount of times i could have reported someone for sexual assault or rape is just beyond a joke. 
and yet i was always scared of what they would do to me, if the justice system failed 'because they have dependants, because they have a career.' i was scared i would end up dead.

not going out running alone does not solve sexual assault and rape. it is everywhere. 
it is even in your home at the hands of your partner.

telling women to not be free is not the answer. there being a serious and absolute penalty for this kind of behaviour is.

#enoughisenough #metoo #womenempoweringwomen

text: rape culture and the ideas around what constitutes rape have been warped for centuries. i think the singular most important thing to know is-if you did not consent to a sexual act that took place is it rape. regardless of whether you were okay with it prior and changed your mind, no means no. rape has many forms and it's important to know if you were sexually violated against your will no matter the circumstances you do not need to feel ashamed, less than whole or hide away because of what you are going through. lastly rape happens to men too, so be aware and stay alert. #rape #rapeculture #rapesurvivor #rapeisrape #sexeducation #nomeansno #metoo #thursdaythoughts

at 3:39 in the afternoon
as my head swam
in doubt filled swells
waiting for the ringing

down the road

to the glaring sod landscape

for 
too long

respoded

text:
impact of online  sexual  harassment 
sexual  harassment of  this  kind (swipe to see ) can make a  person feel any  of the  following :
-threatened  or  scared -exploited -coerced .
-that  their  dignity  is  violated -humiliated or  degraded -shamed or  judged -upset -sexualized -discriminated against because of  their  gender or sexualorientation. -feel  guilty or  that  they are  to blame . 
the experience and  the  impact  of  online  sexual  harassment  is unique to the  individual and  can be  felt both in the  short- term but also  can have long-term impacts  on  mental health and  wellbeing.
.

.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar adaÂ umbrella actÂ lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakanÂ #metooÂ yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, â€œpertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai â€˜amanahâ€™Â beijing platform for actionÂ (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa â€˜kontrol seksualâ€™ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.â€
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagiÂ qawwamÂ (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
â€œmenjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,â€ ungkapnya kepadaÂ mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.

text:
footage of nigel farage swigging a pint and thanking steve bannon and breitbart for the brexit result was deleted from a breitbart youtube channel, following the data scandal surrounding cambridge analytica.
.
- well done bannon, well done breitbart, the ex-ukip leader announces in the short clip. - you helped with this. hugely.

farageâ€™s nod to steve bannon certainly hasnâ€™t aged well in the context of the recent storm around cambridge analyticaâ€™s influence over the eu referendum.

it was revealed that data from 50 million facebook profiles were looked at against the electoral register, and then used to build an algorithm which analyses peopleâ€™s personality traits in relation to their voting behaviour.

this data could then be used to find potential swing voters and create messages tailored to influence them politically.

the firmâ€™s vice president at the time was steve bannon, who was also head of the right-wing website breitbart and was running donald trumpâ€™s campaign to become us president.

anna o'donohue

text:
the symbol of the rising phoenix, means so much to me. it symbolizes my rise from the hell fire i endured in my former life. all the physical, mental and sexual abuses, the poverty, moving every year for my whole life. therefore having no roots. the bullying i endured growing up, always the angry loner and outcast. the trips to the children's psychiatric hospital. all the self hate. all the thoughts and attempts of suicide. all the self sabotage and destruction. all the self inflicted torment. the devastating disease that is addiction and alcoholism. by the grace of god out of these ashes of my former life i have risen, with all the intense fury and rage of the rising sun. for i am the male version of the rising phoenix. i am the warrior of god. i was born in the intense heat and pressure of a living hell. i will not crack, i will take no quarter and none shall be given. god has given me a mission. to save the abused, neglected, bullied and poverty stricken children of this world. i will gladly trade my life for just one child. i pledge my sword and my life to this cause. i pray to die a martyr's death, for there is no greater honor than to die for and in the path of god. know my resolve. know my  commitment. know i want to die a martyr's death. know i am warrior, the warrior of god. know my belief and my faith in god is unshakeable. know i will not and can not be defeated, unless god wills it, for god is with me. may god have no mercy on those that prey on children. may they all burn in hell fire forever....

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaignâ€™s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of peopleâ€™s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there â€œcould have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheatingâ€. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesdayâ€™s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
â€œnoâ€ does not mean â€œconvince meâ€. â€œnoâ€ means no. 
whether itâ€™s because of all the romantic comedies we watch, or the way weâ€™ve been brought up, many of us think that even if the person we like is not interested in us, we should keep trying. the ugly truth is that if someone doesnâ€™t show interest, we arenâ€™t supposed to chase them like lost lambs, hoping theyâ€™ll accept our love someday. we need to be sure enough of ourselves and have the dignity and consideration to let it go. rejections are a part of life. often, when we keep trying to make someone accept us, it is toxic for us and the other person. we feel like we are not good enough for them, or we end up making them uncomfortable and dislike us completely. rejections do not indicate your faults, but how you handle them says a lot about your character. the person rejecting you is not worth your time and effort. and the person rejecting you also has preferences, so unless they are abusive in the way they reject you, their actions are justified. if one persists when the other person is clearly not interested, it could be classified as a case of harassment. let it go. for yourself and others. it may not seem easy at first, but the first step is accepting your rejection, and the rest comes in time. 
good luck and keep blooming, 
s. 
#awareness #harassment #metoo #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness

nope, this is not the â€œ10-year challenge,â€ because this before and after happened over a 1-year timeframeâ€”1992 to 1993 to be exact. and i can thank the latest t.v. bachelor (â€œthe virginâ€) for this post.  i accidentally caught this past mondayâ€™s episode because my last client of the evening cancelled. i guess you could say it was meant to be because this episode took me back to 1992 when the bright-eyed, naive girl (pictured on the left)declared to the world (mainly my college campus) that she was a virgin and saving herself for marriage. as i share in my upcoming book, announcing to the world that you are a virgin (whether you are male or female), not only reeks of â€œiâ€™m holier than you,â€ but it puts a target on your back for predators. over the next year, the girl with the half-closed eyes (pictured on the right) found that out the hard way. your virginity/sexual experience status is no oneâ€™s business but your own. and if you are saving yourself for marriage or abstaining for religious reasons...then keep it between you and god. still not convinced? well, read my soon-to-be-released book--click the link in bio ğŸ‘†to preorder. #victorious #vday â¤ï¸

text:
it breaks my heart to share that on january 28th 2019 kim bok dong grandmother passed away at 93 years old ... i first met her in 2010, both grandma gil and grandma kim lived together at 'our peaceful house' a shelter for survivors of military sexual slavery during wwii. it was through their relationship would i learn how incredibly courageous, supportive and tough grandma kim was. she was in many ways an older sister to grandma gil... she gave me the nickname 'stick fly or fly stick' cause  my english name in korean sounded like that... i had the honor to travel with her to japan and glendale california for the statue reveal, it is through these journeys where i got to see first hand the legend and legacy of grandma kim. since 1992 when she first spoke out to the world about the atrocities committed against her and hundreds of thousands of other young women, she was laying the foundation to what we may now know as the #metoo movement. grandma kim has since dedicated her life to making a change for all of us... thank you  kim bok dong halmoni for your strength and wisdom. we will never forget. <3 .
.
.
#ibelievesurvivors #grandmother #fighter #resilience #nextgeneration #taiwan #og #documentary #activist #courage #bravery

text: whoa. i just survived a 7 day jury trial on a 7 count sexual assault case with a black male defendant and three white female complainants. the twelve jurors duked it out for 7 days from 9-430pm in a windowless room without any breaks. as you can imagine this was a super intense discussion in the me too era + all the racial tension in this country. that jury trial felt like a microcosm of all the problems in the world. there were full scale fights in that room that required the court security to step in. some people were logical, more people were emotional. everyone was opinionated. we found the defendant not guilty on 2 charges and we were undecided on the other 5 counts so the judge declared the case a mistrial. i hope we came to the correct verdict for all parties involved. all i know is that although iâ€™m exhausted, i now secretly want to be a criminal defense attorney. ğŸ˜‚#metoo #juryduty #civicresponsibility #dotherightthing

from the first march for empowerment and equality to the #metoo movement, women have come a long way in shattering boundaries... today's media, especially give women the freedom and opportunity to wield their batons beyond any boundaries! with an ode to the media as women's potent tool for empowerment, we welcome the second edition of media mahakumbh, which celebrates the transition of women from fitting into glass slippers to shattering glass ceilings.

text:
@ocasio2018 talks about her attitude towards fear and speaking up as a freshman member of the 116th congress..
.
"itâ€™s always intimidating to speak up in a new setting. in congress, we abide by strict rules of communication, particularly in committee. for example, youâ€™re supposed to address the chair, and speak in the third person when referring to your colleagues. breaking these rules can have consequences small and large: not knowing how means you could lose precious speaking time, or miss an opportunity to make a point. opposing party members are always looking for the slightest slip-up to gum up process or make an example of you.
.
so yes, speaking up for the first time in this environment can be scary. hereâ€™s my trick: for a long time, iâ€™ve used fear as a guiding light ğŸ’¡ instead of a reason to turn off. emotions are information and data too, and fear is telling us something. for me, fear isnâ€™t saying â€œgo away,â€ fear tells me â€œthis is new, and it *could* be dangerous. there are are stakes here.â€ but iâ€™ve very frequently interpreted fear as a growth cusp. aside from some concrete fears, we often donâ€™t know what weâ€™re afraid of until we get there, and feel it. fear tells us how to grow. fear, like a lot of discomfort, forces us to choose: â€œdo i do this, or not?â€ without fear, there is no courage. without fear, we donâ€™t have the opportunity to prove ourselves in ways we never thought possible.
.
so while we often think of fear as a signal to retreat, it can also be the opportunity to leap."
.
.
.
.
.

text:
today, all workplaces in india are mandated by law to provide a safe and secure working environment free from sexual harassment for all women. but this wasn't the case until in 2013 when the posh (prevention of sexual harassment) act came into existence, which was driven by the popular case of bhanwari devi, a rural level change agent, who in the year 1992 was engaged by the state of rajasthan as aÂ sathinÂ to work towards the prevention of the practice of child marriages. during the course of her work, she attracted harassment from men of that community. she reported this to the local authority but no action was taken, and she was subsequently gang-raped by those very men.
.
when this cased was presented before the supreme court of india as a pil (public interest litigation), the supreme court realised the need to recognize sexual harassment as a violation of women's fundamental right to equality, and that all workplaces / establishments / insitutions be made accountable and responsible to uphold these rights.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

#preventionofsexualharassment #workplacelaws #posh #beartsy #metoo #mentalassault #mentalharassment #instaworkplace #instaoffice #feminism #feminist #timesup #believesurvivors #womensreality #whyididntreport  #itsnotokay
name: Be.artsy: Emotions at Work

today, all workplaces in india are mandated by law to provide a safe and secure working environment free from sexual harassment for all women. but this wasn't the case until in 2013 when the posh (prevention of sexual harassment) act came into existence, which was driven by the popular case of bhanwari devi, a rural level change agent, who in the year 1992 was engaged by the state of rajasthan as aÂ sathinÂ to work towards the prevention of the practice of child marriages. during the course of her work, she attracted harassment from men of that community. she repoed this to the local authority but no action was taken, and she was subsequently gang-raped by those very men.
.
when this cased was presented before the supreme cou of india as a pil (public interest litigation), the supreme cou realised the need to recognize sexual harassment as a violation of women's fundamental right to equality, and that all workplaces / establishments / insitutions be made accountable and responsible to uphold these rights.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text: okay so the good news is the energies cosmically will also be supporting this shift- more to come on this more hopeful energies! i promise i will create another post tomorrow that highlights the brighter side of this weekend, and trust me itâ€™s going to help us move forward! as challenging as this may feel, trust the process now more than ever. those who have leaped, you got this- donâ€™t be fooled by the amount of work it entails to get unstuck from old situations no longer serving you. the hardest part was leaping, but we are not even close to the complete shift. breathe, have fun, and stay healthy and sharp, allow your body rest, grief, and exercise. be proud of yourself and honor the changes and resistance to changes that are occurring within and without. for those that are still holding themselves back from that leap, you will find these energies to be more of a challenge, even feeling overwhelmed by it all. breathe, you still have the opportunity to change your path- we always do. it may be harder the more we dig our heels in, however, if you accept the things you can not change, and have the courage to change the things you can- healing will occur, and transformation inevitably follows. there is no right or wrong path- thatâ€™s the beauty of life. we just think there is. are we choosing to look at our past experiences as mistakes or lessons? the power is within us all to create a shift from fear to love. it is a collective need and the divide we see across the world and in our own country is a manifestation of this truth. light needs dark. dark needs light. offering compassion while being firm in our conviction to hold those that create harm to others accountable. change starts within. be the change you wish to see in the world (gandhi). and live and let live.

text:
this term first appeared or started being used around 12th century and it was mostly used to describe an unmarried woman. nowadays, we use it to describe someone who has not had any type of sexual activity. 
first: it is not biological. there is no biological way to determine someone's virginity because you can't tell if a male has ever had sex and a female body's hymen can break from wearing tampons, riding a bike, or it may have never existed in the first place. that's just the magic of biology. everyone's born differently. 
two: everyone has sex differently. not everyone has sex by inserting a penis inside a vagina so the heterosexual norm of "virginity" usually implies this. so does that mean gay men or women won't lose their virginity? what about people who are paraplegic or quadriplegic? 
three: the idea that this is something we can "lose" puts a lot of pressure on all of  us. it pressures young people when they hear all of their classmates are "doing it" and fear they are behind developmentally. it puts emotional harm to victims of rape and assault when the concept is placed in a pedestal and society now views them as a tarnished object which has lost something. let's be honest, the concept views one group as the winners and one group as the losers when it comes to virginity.

text:
today we released two more blog posts to the nightingale from nilsa rivera and rachel. read a little about each of their essays and then click the link in our bio to read the full blog posts! 
in nilsa riveraâ€™s essay, â€œthe word rape is made of tarâ€, rivera does the difficult work of dissecting the word â€œrapeâ€-not entirely in its meaning but â€œthe sight of the word, the visual, almost physical, three-dimensional representation of itâ€. with this essay, rivera hopes to encourage her readers to think deeply about how the intricacies of language can affect us. 
rachel is no stranger to awakenings as we are lucky enough have her multimedia piece, "complex trauma: a memoirâ€ currently on display. now, we want to share her literary talents! her essay, â€œwe need to break through the silence on abuses of institutionalized childrenâ€, explores the systematic abuse and sexual abuse of institutionalized people from both a personal and objective perspective. she recognizes that " the lack of public outcry, the state-sponsored abuse and even the murder of people with psychological disabilities is a pattern" and hopes that her essay will begin to break the silence surrounding this epidemic.
.
.
.
.
.
#chicagoart #chicagononprofit #chicagogallery #advocacy#survivorart #artsed#artwatchers #metoo#believesurvivors #metoomvmt #consent #creativewriting

text:
an athlete's silence

i am creating a voice for sexually abused athletes by breaking my silence and sharing my experiences that i faced as a springboard and platform diver. i need everyone's help. i have launched a kickstarter campaign to help with publication cost of the sequel to surface tension, entitled, out-cast: the hollywood years and the re-branding of surface tension so they can be released at the same time. the campaign runs for a limited time, 15 days left. if we can get 650 people to donate $10, we will reach the goal and everyone will receive an e-book as soon as it is published. there are other donating levels, please see the link below. 
https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/john-michaellander/out-cast-the-hollywood-years?ref=project_build&fbclid=iwar3q7px2faozb899kuxjbjs3urskhnw_u7tleov7ya7dezwnpknhfsfixig

this book will continue following the main character, david matthew, and the effects sexual abuse has on his everyday life as he tries to break into the entertainment business. i have decided to tell my story through david's eyes. this story extremely relevant to today with #metoo movement and issues facing us gymnastics and osu. but it tells the story from a male's point of view, which our society deems not to recognize as a real problem. i hope that you can help me promote my kickstarter campaign. 
surface tension is available on amazon, and i have shared my story, "an athlete's silence" at tedxdayton 2018:

https://www.amazon.com/surface-tension-john-michael-lander-ebook/dp/b071zqmybn/ref=sr_1_2?crid=3bqi2wmyluogc&keywords=john-michael+lander&qid=1547994106&sprefix=john-michael%2caps%2c136&sr=8-2  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1-4yh82pqia

i am extremely passionate about helping survivors recognize the effects of abuse later in life.  i have been talking with safe sport, army of survivors, and breaking the silence. i would love to include you and/or business in helping me reach the kickstarter campaign goal so i can share my story and my passion of helping others recognize the long-term effects of sexual abuse.

#sexabusesurvivor #sexabuse
#fightsexabuse
#athlete #metoo
#metoomovement #breakthesilence #safesport #safespaces4youth

text:
on march 3, 2018, i was a 2nd-year jet program assistant language teacher (alt) in sasebo, nagasaki, japan. my priorities at the time were simple: enjoy japan while i could. it was my last year on the program and i only had four months left before i returned to the u.s.
my assailant was a 4th-year jet alt from london. he was everyoneâ€™s friend, the fun guy at the party, a mentor/sempai in our community. while i was still struggling to learn basic japanese, he excelled in three years to conversational fluency.

text:
i love my friend @plexxaglass so much and she just debuted a powerful new music video she directed for her song "ana themaâ€ over at @ghettoblastermagazine. please watch!

her words:
â€œi was visited by a ghost, but not in the way you'd think; this wasn't your traditional haunting. the #metoo movement was fresh on everyonesâ€™ minds â€” i'd come forward about my experience with an ex-boyfriend from my high school years. then ana came to me, dressed in turn-of-the-century garb, pale as a ghost, in what i can only describe as a lucid dream, and she told me her story. we were by the sea and she was about to drown herself. she made me promise to tell her story, so that's what i've done here. and hey, it could've been just a dream, this story could be fiction, but i think we can all agree that it's not at all unfamiliar.â€

text:
my time and happiness is the most important thing in my life now.  i work a full time job, that i love going to daily.  i run a side business doing what i love to do. i have my nights free after 4pm on the weekdays and my weekends free.  that gives me a lot of time to spread out with my family, my side business and time for myself.  i wouldnâ€™t trade that for any amount of money. not even a million dollars to have all of that taken from me.

value your time.  you can do what i do and be happy.  you can run a side business in marketing and work full time and still have time with your family and for yourself. 
we all meet the minimum requirements to succeed in life.  its what you do with it and how you do it for you to succeed.  the struggle i can guarantee youâ€™ll have, but without that, you will not succeed!
#metoo
#loveyourself
#youcan
#youareenough
#pathwayscoretraining
#mystory

text:
"how to stop shoulding on yourself" --> the "s" word live (making sales simple & fun)

i am sharing with you something that has been coming up quite frequently with my paying clients and today there is a lively conversation going on about this very thing in my free facebook group.

goal: consider these 3 things so that you can avoid
burnout
overwhelm
going out of business 
questions: 
do you know anyone who puts a ton of pressure on themselves?

have you ever heard a friend, relative or your inner mean girl say out loud "you know what you should do"? do you find yourself having a neverending "to do" list?

#metoo

i have been in charge of my own schedule for over two decades. speaking from the perspective of having messed this part up a lot . . . i am sharing 3 things to consider when we feel like we should be doing this ... or that ... or something else.

1. the task fits the time.

2. consider the daily rhythms like a waldorf preschooler. 
3. give yourself some grace. you are only one person.

give yourself an #attagirl

take a moment and see what you have accomplished this past two days, two weeks, two months . . . you are incredible. 
let's continue the conversation --> https://m.me/renee.hribar?ref=convo

text:
have you spotted our tarc ads around town? post and tag us if you do! help spread the word about our tarcâ€™s ride to safety program which provides free transportation for anyone who needs to get to the center for women and families.
=========================
get onto any tarc bus in louisville or southern indiana and tell the driver you need a ride to safety. you do not need money or a tarc ticket; the ride is free. the driver will arrange for a tarc employee to meet the bus somewhere on its route who will transport you in a car to the center for women and families. you can use this free service if youâ€™re by yourself or if you have your children with you.
==========================
for information on tarc stops and routes, visit www.ridetarc.org or pick-up a route schedule at one of the many information stands across louisville and southern indiana.

for more information about the center for women and families and the ride to safety program, call our toll-free crisis line at 1-844-237-2331.

text:
v a g i n a s | okay, let's talk vaginas! february is the month where i'm focusing my attention to supporting & minimising the impact of my #vulvodynia #vaginismus - something i developed after being raped & after have a very intense trigger during sex - so i can bang more often.

so what is it? vulvodynia is basically on going pain + discomfort in your vulva because it is constantly in a "fright or flight" mode. meaning that there's an increased amount of nerve-endings that are on a constant hyperactive loop. and should anything try to work it's way into my vagina, it's little opening muscles go into overdrive and won't budge (this also means that if the willy does get inside, it does not have a nice experience trying to get out). it also means it feels like burning fire should anything touch because it's not use to the bloodlfow. 
physical health & nutrition are factors that pull into it being less sore as it allows the muscles to relax & break their loop. i'm also seeing a pelvic floor physiotherapist who tries to help desensitise the tissue & muscles. there is no real cure, just these little bits that need to worked on daily.  i'll be focusing my attention to lower body & pelvic floor this month to try alleviate & get some bang times in.

text:
the first time i had a panic attack i was in the middle of my nutrition 101 class. â €
â €
we were watching a video on cardiovascular health which showed rather graphic segments of an angioplasty. the room started to spin, not really an unusual feeling, i have condition called noncardiovascularsyncopy. which essentially means, sometimes gravity works against my system, and i pass out. itâ€™s not rare, many people suffer from this, though i was told most people â€˜grow out of itâ€™ by the time they turn 18. i was 20 at the time. â €
â €
i left the classroom: head spinning, heart pounding, stomach in my throat.. at least i wasnâ€™t driving this time. lying down was suppose to help and though the hallwayâ€™s cold, musty tile felt like bliss, it wasnâ€™t doing a thing to calm me. it was a panic attack.â €
â €
i would like to say it was the last one, but even six years later they are ongoing- though less frequent. learning what my triggers are has been the most helpful in learning how to control or anticipate when i may have one.â €
â €
it took me way too long to figure out one of my biggest triggers is heart health. i used to just say it â€œfreaks me outâ€ like i could do nothing besides call it an irrational fear but was it irrational? i looked deeper, and i realized i was so afraid because i was not taking control of myself and of my heart. now i focus my weight, i control what i put into my body, i do my cardio, i meditate. this is my time to be selfish and exhale the bullshit that iâ€™ve been putting myself through. this is the time for me. â €

hi everyone! there are a lot of new faces around here and i wanted to introduce myself for those who donâ€™t know me yet. i am fabiana, an east coast girl living in a west coast world. i am a certified therapeutic recreation specialist (ctrs), entrepreneur, and wellness enthusiast. i also work for senior living company. 
i am 1 of 5 kids and the only girl. yeah i loved every minute of being the only girl! i married @williamgould82 about 2.5 years ago. we enjoy traveling, cooking together and using essential oils. we have and love our fur babies mandi-love and cali faith. 
i am passionate about working with seniors and helping them live their best life at this stage in their life. i am also very passionate about educating others on living a chemical free life to live a life above the wellness line. .

text:
the backstreet boys have a new album out. itâ€™s all over my twitter feed. a few years ago i wouldâ€™ve been excited along with all the other fans. now i get a pit in my stomach, because all i can think about is my brave sister survivor @themelissaschuman. another trigger for her to have to endure. another reminder of her rapist & what he did to her. i know how painful it is for me to remember & relive my assault. i can only imagine how horrible it is for melissa because her rapist is famous & beloved.
today i went back and read her incredibly brave and vulnerable blog post. the post that gave her a platform to share her story. the post where she detailed the pain of the assault and the pain sheâ€™s lived with afterwards. the post that propelled her into the spotlight and made her a target for bsb fans. threats, hate mail, and even suspicious packages sent to her home. all because she told the truth.

..

your feelings are not facts and your thoughts are not facts either. be aware of that and the fact others may believe how they feel and think is what is true even though it isn't. ğŸ‘ŒğŸ»

text:
very few people know my story, know my traumas. i donâ€™t share them often, not because they donâ€™t deserve their truth being spoken, but because it makes others uncomfortable, and iâ€™m a people pleaser. so i stay silent. what good does it do, though, to not show people all of me? my childhood, horrible as it was, is part of who i am, for better or worse. so here goes. â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
â¤ï¸â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
i haven't had an easy life. i was sexually abused for several years as a child, and emotionally and mentally abused for even longer, by my father. before this last year started, i had always lived my life according to how others told me i had to. i was ugly because i was told i was. i was unlovable because i was told i was. i wasn't wanted and would never be because i was told over and over that i wasn't in the first place. i was wicked because horrendous things happened to me and i didn't "do" anything to stop it, so i must have wanted them to happen. (to put it into perspective, i was seven when it started, and was, in my mind, taken from my mother and the only family i knew up until then). i deserved what i got because i was who i was, and it would never change. years of lies and harsh words can seriously damage your psyche, and it may never be healed regardless of how intelligent you are or how much you know better. i didn't deserve love, a good life, or good moments. this was the life i had to endure. my identity was wrapped around what someone else told me i was, so that identity was twisted and warped. â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
â¤ï¸â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
the person who is supposed to be your first line of defense is the one who is slowly killing you. iâ€™ve grown into the person i am, and i am awesome in spite of him. â¤ï¸â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €

text:
wise words from @elizabeth_smart_official
ğŸ’
a bill was introduced yesterday in our state to protect a child from an abusive parent. 977 children walked through the doors of our childrenâ€™s advocacy center last year with reports of abuse. that is almost a thousand children in one small county of our state. this is a huge problem. @rainn says that the perpetrator of most child sexual abuse cases is a parent. according to @d2lorg only 19-29% of child sexual abuse reports even result in an arrest. @childhelp warns that this is a huge hidden epidemic.
âœ¨
putting a child back into the care of an abusive parent can at the least lead to toxic stress and at the worst, as we see too many times in the news, lead to a devastating outcome.
âœ¨
if you havenâ€™t heard of the adverse childhood experience (aces) study, iâ€™m attaching a link and hope you will learn more about it. basically it is adding up the harmful experiences a child has endured in their life and the higher the number the greater risk that child will have a multitude of problems later in life. arkansas has one of the highest ace scores in the nation. toxic stress associated with forcing a child to be with someone they are afraid of or could potentially hurt them will only add to our ace scores.
âœ¨
we combat aces with trauma informed systems that you get by having trauma informed policies. having statewide uniform policies that inform and guide those involved in making decisions affecting a child ensure that no matter what the childâ€™s zip code is and what court system they find themselves in, the child is protected.
âœ¨
a parent should never be forced to hand over their scared child to the person that abused them. a child should never be afraid to go home, should never be afraid to go to sleep not knowing what might happen to them in the middle of the night, and they should never be afraid of the one person in the world that should protect them the most.
ğŸ’

text:
when weâ€™ve experienced a trauma, starting over can feel like the a burden far too heavy to bear. .
.
but we can. you can. starting anew can happen every day, every hour, every second â€” if that is whatâ€™s needed. .
.
what does it mean to start over? does it â€˜haveâ€™ to be a huge undertaking? if it feels like it, where did that expectation come from? .
.
a little less than 2 weeks ago, i was rear-ended on the freeway at a high speed. had i not been wearing a seat belt or left ample space between me and the car in front of me, i would have likely been severely injured or crushed between a semi truck and the cars immediately behind and in front of me. my nearly brand new car totaled. back and neck injured, but no broken bones. .
.
car accidents, job losses, deaths of loved ones, domestic and sexual violence, psychological abuse; these and more can be terrifying and traumatic events that leave us feeling paralyzed. what i think i did not realize personally is although i felt paralyzed, i was still making moves to put pieces back together. even if it was simply saying to a friend or loved one that i needed help or a shoulder to lean on. even if i took one extra deep breath for myself. i was starting again and kept moving forward. .
.
healing is not linear, and yours will not look like mine or anyone elseâ€™s. to anyone needing to read this today: starting anew is a moment by moment or breath-by-breath process if we need it to be. no one deserves your love and kindness more than you. .
.

text:
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar adaÂ umbrella actÂ lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakanÂ #metooÂ yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, â€œpertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai â€˜amanahâ€™Â beijing platform for actionÂ (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa â€˜kontrol seksualâ€™ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.â€
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagiÂ qawwamÂ (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
â€œmenjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,â€ ungkapnya kepadaÂ mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.
â€”â€”

text:
â€œi canâ€™t stand feministsâ€œ

that was from a 17 year old girl at the gym.

her and her mother were debating the womenâ€™s movement. mum was coming from the old school & her daughter the new school.

then they turned to me sitting there sweaty after a class asking for an opinion on this matter.

mum was wagging her finger and daughter was getting wide eyed as the seconds ticked away. 
it was definitely a tough conversation to enter into.

so i entered into it... depends if the feminist is coming to help people become accountable for their actions or coming from a victim mentality looking for revenge.

a feminist victim is someone who hasnâ€™t had a voice in childhood & so when challenged or pushed brings out that suppressed voice by rallying with others for support to something they havenâ€™t dealt with in themselves. 
they come across as activist behind a cause fuelled by deep resentment.

they can hide easily because they usually stand behind some injustice thatâ€™s happened to them or to a group of people theyâ€™re associated with.

michelle obama is a healthy expression whereas the feminist victim gathers others to make themselves feel the power they missed out on having.

the cause can be admirable but all that hidden resentment can come flooding out when an opportunity presents itself for a person who has been persecuted ( victim). iâ€™ve had 3 people in seminars pull the victim card out & because theyâ€™re not easy to spot only appear when they think an injustices has popped up they can evade detection. 
they once were the innocent child 
they once had a heart of love & pure light 
pushed down by the parent , teacher or guide 
now to become an unhealed victim 
resentful 
hidden behind a smile , an image or a cause but hiding deep pain & resentment.

goodie goods. 
all love and light hiding dark resentments usually with a lot of physical conditions that represent the resentments physically stored in the body.

to come back they must find their own power again and own it. to become the hero they lost long ago.

to bring the victim to the victor & overcome the need to destroy what held that love down.

and so we sat and talked debated & questioned until it was all too

.
.
so, while it could have gone better, i still moved and did what i could. i also faced more fears - lateral jumping.  anyone who has seen me at the crossfit box knows i donâ€™t/wonâ€™t do lateral jumps much. itâ€™s a mind-over-matter thing and they are scary, hard, and terrible.  yet another weakness iâ€™m working on. .
.
iâ€™ll count today as a smiley face ğŸ˜€ like we use at @crossfit_i1uvit when you try your best and thatâ€™s all we can ask for the day. not focusing on time, reps or rounds. just effort.  i count today as 1% better mentally, so thatâ€™s a win.

text:
perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, â€œpertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai â€˜amanahâ€™ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa â€˜kontrol seksualâ€™ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.â€ kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. â€œmenjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,â€ ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, â€œtidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,â€ tukasnya.[] sumber:www.muslimahnews.com

text:
itâ€™s me v me
.
i donâ€™t compete with anyone but myself. i donâ€™t compete for times.
.
i compete to see what iâ€™m capable of. i compete to see how far i can go. i compete to see what this beautiful body is able to accomplish.
.
itâ€™s me v me.
itâ€™s mind v heart.
itâ€™s mental strength v my old friends anxiety, panic and depression.
.
this time iâ€™m going to beat them.
in this little corner of my house i find the solitude, self confidence, peace, strength, grit and rediscover my endurance.
.
ironman training isnâ€™t fancy. itâ€™s grit. itâ€™s what you do when nobody else is around and looking. i love training alone. itâ€™s meditation for me. itâ€™s healing me to my bones these days. itâ€™s giving me fire to fight.
.
todayâ€™s ironman training was:
60 minutes on the bike that i dragged and set up on my trainer at my kidâ€™s soccer practice. it was an ass kicker ğŸ˜ˆğŸš´ğŸ»â€â™€ï¸
.
then day 3 of my half marathon running program. it was 2x12 mins with 4 min walk between. my incline was at 1% and i did 90 seconds at 12 min/mile - 30 seconds at 10 min/mile. repeated 6x each section.
.
iâ€™m feeling more and more confidence in running and falling back in love with it each time. itâ€™s sooooooooo exhilarating to be doing what i love again and feeling adrenaline and peace instead of anxiety! iâ€™m really happy again doing this and i may be over emphasizing this all but itâ€™s my journey back to an athlete and iâ€™m soooooo proud because last summer i could barely move. iâ€™m sharing this journey, this story, this training in all its nitty gritty glory because itâ€™s accountability for me and this time it means more than ever to cross that finish line at ironman chattanooga. ğŸ™ğŸ½ğŸ–¤
.
iâ€™ve done the mental and spiritual work the past 18 months and it feels pretty fucking good to be doing the physical work now. #ironmantraining #metoo #ironmanchattanooga #veganathlete

posted @withrepost â€¢ @frizzkidart today's affirmation art: all survivors are brave. all victims are brave. ğŸ’› those who share their stories of surviving sexual violence/intimate partner violence are brave, but those who may not be able to share their stories or don't want to are also brave. no survivor/victim is cowardly and it's their choice what they want to do with their story. you may also wonder why i chose to include the word "victim." not everyone who experiences sexual violence or intimate partner violence feels like a "survivor." if we want to approach this issue in a "survivor-centric" way, then we can't impose the same strong, recovery, survival narrative on every person impacted by sexual violence/ipv. every survivor/victim is different, navigates their trauma differently, and has different perspectives on justice and healing looks like. in looking at the #metoo movement, i've seen a tendency to want to tell all stories the same way, without realizing that all survivors/victims have different intersections in their identity that a) impacts their likelihood to experience violence and b) changes the way experience justice and reconciliation with trauma. every survivor/victim is worthy of love, respect, and support. every survivor/victim is brave no matter how they choose to cope with their trauma. #art #artist #affirmation #illustration #drawing #draw #healing #heal #justice #metoo #feministart #endrapeculture #selflove #brave #torontoartist #feminist

text:
perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks  pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, â€œpertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai â€˜amanahâ€™ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa â€˜kontrol seksualâ€™ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.â€ kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. â€œmenjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,â€ ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, â€œtidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,â€ tukas

kekerasan seksual . pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks ,  peama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal . muatan srhr ( sexual reproductive health right ) sebagai â€˜ amanah â€™ beijing platform action ( bpfa ) amat kuat . frasa â€˜ kontrol seksual â€™ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur . termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun .  kedua , kata pratma julia , merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri . tak ada lagi qawwam ( pemimpin ) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat . ketiga , menikam syariat islam . kalangan liberal , dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah .  menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata ,  ungkapnya kepada mnews , rabu ( 30/1/2019 ) . pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan ,  tidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual , bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak . syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya ,  tukas

i've mentioned lots of silver linings i've found through the bs that is this brca journey - all you lovely people i've connected with, a better understanding of my health...i could go on. but the other night something new and wonderful occurred to me. 
i was talking to one of my closest friends, also a survivor of sexual trauma and it occured to me... this new chest that i'm learning to love a little more everyday... my attacker has never  and will never lay eyes or vile claws on it. and somehow now i feel magically whole again, in a way i havent in over a decade. kind of amazing actually.

text:
after nearly 12 years of very active embodied healing of myself and nearly a decade of working with mostly women on mind-body-spirit healing and empowerment (you name it...relationship issues, phobias, childhood sexual abuse and incest to serious negative entity attachments to sex trafficking prevention advocacy), something i never in a million years would have guessed happened to me on one of my many trips to #nyc last year. .

i was #violated. .

my body went into a momentary freeze, shock state. i just could not believe it. donâ€™t think of the worst thing ever here. but it wasnâ€™t fun, iâ€™ll tell you that. 
bc of all the work iâ€™ve done and continue to do on myself and bc of my extensive trainings and studies in somatic and breath based trauma healing and meditation, i actually had a choice which is rare here. but i saw i had worked my ass off for this moment: i could let the incident trigger a deep state of terror within me and bring me back to my many years of being absolutely terrified of the world (all the while appearing aggressive and seductive so you wouldnâ€™t know itâ€”unconsciously existing in one big trauma reenactment) or i could say, â€œok god/spirit/allah, what exactly are you up to here? why this bs after all these years and why now during our #metoo time?â€ within an hour of #heartrhythmmeditation , i got the message: a clear download of what needed to be done. .
within a day of returning to pa, i called up @wannabe_wandering and said, â€œhey....i had this vision, and it goes something like this....â€and she said, â€œthatâ€™s funny, i just had the same vision in my dream the other night.â€ so there you have it folks. me too berks: a time to heal (empowrong all people) was born. for more on what happened in nyc, please join me and tara for a powerful event at the miller center in march 30th. 
this is a movement that invites a shift in the conversation away from persecution and into inclusivity, healing, prevention and education. .
website is www.metooberks.com and the fb page link in my bio above! iâ€™d be so profoundly grateful for all you local to se pa if you could help us share any of these me too posts and invite people on fb to our events! ğŸ™

text:
girls in pain get less sympathy
vidcast: https://youtu.be/_w3hodgjfp0

another goal for the #metoo movement is suggested by the latest study from yale psychologists.  as research subjects observed a video of the very same child being subjected to the classic, old fashioned medical torture, the fingerstick, but identified as either samuel or samantha, the majority of observers, both men and women, believe that the girl samantha felt less pain than the boy samuel.

this gender bias result is in synch with similar impressions of adults experiencing pain.  the result can be explained by the widespread misconception that boys are more stoic than girls, and it would take greater pain to elicit the same response in the male. 
parents of girls and significant others of women undergoing procedures need to advocate for their child or partner if they feel that the  pain management being offered is insufficient whether or not itâ€™s due to gender bias. 
brian d earp, joshua t monrad, marianne lafrance, john a bargh, lindsey l cohen, jennifer a richeson. gender bias in pediatric pain assessment. journal of pediatric psychology, 2019; doi: 10.1093/jpepsy/jsy104

text_retweet:
reposted from @backto_muslimidentity -  perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks  pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, â€œpertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai â€˜amanahâ€™ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa â€˜kontrol seksualâ€™ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.â€ kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. â€œmenjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,â€ ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, â€œtidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,â€ tukasnya.[] sumber:www.mu

repairing intuition.

intuition is a wonderful gift. intuition is that 6th sense; that feeling we get from our bodies telling us something is happening or is going to happen based on everything we have experienced in our lives thus far.

itâ€™s the warning sign giving us a headâ€™s up. sometimes we choose to ignore our intuition. 
why? 
is it denial? 
is it fear? 
is it that we donâ€™t want to do the difficult thing in that moment and put up a boundary?

ignoring intuition stems from us learning to not trust ourselves. 
whether this was low self-esteem baked into us as children or having unhealthy relationships that made us second guess ourselves. 
itâ€™s important to understand why we ignore our intuition first and then learn to trust our intuition and know that itâ€™s there to guide us and that we can, and have a right, to act on it without any explanation. 
because trusting yourself to follow your intuition will not lead you astray.

we spotted this mother heading into the slaughterhouse this morning, her throat was already slit and her blood had been drained.

we will likely never know the reason why she was killed before being taken to the slaughterhouse or what happened during her final moments alive.

we do however know what her time alive will have been like.

dairy cows live a life of constant torment.

they are pregnant for 3/4 of the year and have every calf removed immediately after being born.

she spent the majority of her life knowing that her unborn child would be taken from her.

now her lifeless body lays in the back of this truck, broken and spent, she will soon end up incinerated.
.

text:
reviewing book 13th for 2019ğŸŒ¸
.
so i will be posting daily from now onwards and have been planning to take february on a more creative path. 
plus yaay it's my birthday month.
.
it's official, stupid by sid baliga is a blend of a corporate #metoo story and a true love story. 
the story starts with astitha joining the corporate world and as she falls head over heels for her manager mr. joby joseph she is taken aback to her college memories and romance. the flashbacks of her and her college romantic sumanth tells us that sumanth was deeply in love with astitha however due to bad health and no career goals astitha decided to dump sumanth. astitha's manager mr. joby is mesmerized by astitha and confesses her that he truly liked her and their relationship takes a step ahead from the corporate relationship they already shared. just as the relationship of joby and astitha takes a start, sumanth is destined to meet astitha and come back in her life. the story makes us believe that joby and astitha may end up together as their love was already noticeable by the other corporate colleagues  and family. however not until astitha goes missing and sumanth turns restless and joby seems too formal. that's when the #metoo  story is revealed and  sumanth's true love is appreciated.
the story is pretty relatable with the real life incidences however the story needed to be defined a little more precisely. 
the title of the book is cool and the cover too is pretty. 
rating: ğŸŒŸğŸŒŸğŸŒŸ/5

- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking â€˜ugh. totally uglyâ€™ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itâ€™s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donâ€™t necessarily know itâ€™s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itâ€™s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youâ€™re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleâ€™s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnâ€™t have seen, and couldnâ€™t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, â€œwould work for anyoneâ€. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyâ€™re mercenaries. theyâ€™ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itâ€™s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing â€“ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public â€“ our intimate family connections, our â€œlikesâ€, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatâ€™s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer". in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field." despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
huge news for the team at @wayfarerla i am so excited for them!  fourteen months ago i entrusted my #metoo story to a group of strangers in los angeles.

i was extremely thankful to get the trauma out of my system that was my personal reward. to take my power back and feel cleansed of the experience.

i am thankful i listened to a dear friend and made the right choice to share my story to this team.

congratulations to the team at wayfarer entertainment i am so thankful for your vision and courage.

more impact, stories and opportunity. this is great news! #beingkarenalston #wayfarerentertainment #dreambigger #makenosmallplans #socialimpact #justinbaldoni #storytelling #impactfunds #metoo

text:
you said that you loved me
tell me why does it feel 
like a thousand tiny cuts 
cascading across my skin 
why does it feel like love is just a weapon
you wield to keep me locked in

all this time later 
still feels like yesterday 
pieces of me 
caught in the fray
i have nothing left to say 
heart weighted down by hate 
peeling back the layers of my rage
broken and betrayed 
but i refuse to stay that way
light awaits 
i cannot say how long this wound
will remain 
can only love me back to me again â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€” poem by marley monroe/ ğŸ“¸photographer: marley monroe// recovery comes in baby steps. sorrow, in waves. all i know is i will not stop until all of me emanates light once again, and i will not let what right now feels like a trauma that defines me, take over my heart. ğŸ’–ğŸ¦‹ #photography #poetsofinstagram #poetry #photographer #lyrics #metoo #poetrycommunity #singersongwriter #singersofinstagram #sunsets

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
this photo popped up on my facebook as being posted 1 year ago today, timely given i arrived back in istanbul yesterday.

the caption was:
"
watching those around me return to europe for christmas and new year i began to miss this summer season in australia. being so far away it was a difficult decision to make, as i picked apart the pros and cons of forking out for a flight home and how i felt i was quitting or somehow failing for returning.
i reminded myself i don't have anything to prove and that summer is a wonderful time of year in australia. now i am essentially holidaying in my home country: reading loads of books, connecting with nature and seeing the people i love ğŸ–ğŸ“š
"

last year was a massive year of transformation, primarily spiritually and around self love, but on top of that i was also suffering pretty severe ptsd from a sexual assult while travelling.

i am so grateful to my support network, i deeply love you and cannot express what you mean to me. my moving to canberra was an accidental and clearly necessary part of my healing and i miss and think about you all a lot.

@kiah.s @heymilicuda_ @lauralilliann @strippermonologues @mallory_berryman @qqquiet @sinafever @deeeids 
now here i am back in my favourite city, ğŸ•Œâ˜•istanbulğŸ‡¹ğŸ‡·â„ , just over a year later. i am not a failure, my life is so incredibly wild and adventurous and i am so proud of myself for being so open to change and growth.

text_retweet:
reposted from @backto_muslimidentity -  perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks  pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, â€œpertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai â€˜amanahâ€™ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa â€˜kontrol seksualâ€™ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.â€ kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. â€œmenjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,â€ ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, â€œtidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,â€ tukasnya.[] sumber:www.mu
